text:
I wanted to show you all these animals, but
it's raining.

Let's sing the Mr. Sun song and maybe the
sun will shine.
Mr. Sun sun, hello Mr. Sun.
Mr. Sun sun, hello Mr. Sun.
Come on and let's go see the horse.
And what do horses say yeah?
Mrs. Horse horse, hello Mrs. Horse.
Please will you neigh for me.
Let's go and see, if the cows are okay.
Mrs. Cow cow, hello Mrs. Cow.

Please will 
you moo for me.
Moo moo moo moo moo moo moo.
So can you tell me what color are the cows?
You know the colors, don't you.
Come on, say it with me.
Let's go and see pigs before they change color.
But hey what do pigs say?
Let's sing the song to Mrs. Pig.
Mrs. Pig pig, hello Mrs. Pig.
Please will you oink for me.
Oink oink oink oink oink oink.
Oh look up on the hill.
So the sheep haven't changed color.

Come on, let's go and find out what's happening
on this crazy farm.

I'm disguised as a sheep to find out what's
going on on this crazy farm.
Oh you know what a sheep says, don't you.
Hello Mrs. Sheep, let's sing our song.
Mrs. Sheep sheep, hello Mrs. Sheep.
Please will you bleat for me.

Let's find out what's really going on on this
farm.
Let's change the color of the sheep.
She's taking the colors out of the rainbow.
I have to stop that naughty naughty bird.

It's me and I'm red like these sheep and that
just crazy.
I don't want to be red.
Put all the colors back in the rainbow now.
A colorful rainbow on a sunny day.
Let's sing our song one last time.
Mr. Sun sun, hello Mr. Sun.
Mr. Sun sun, hello Mr. Sun.
Maggie, what a naughty naughty bird.
See you next time boys and girls.
I'm going to the park to meet Maggie.
I know a song that we can sing to the sun.
If you know it, join me.
Mr. Sun sun, hello Mr. Sun.
Mr. Sun sun, hello Mr. Sun.
Let's go and meet Maggie at the park.
Mr. Dog dog, hello Mr. Dog.
Please will you bark for me.
Please back for me Mr. Dog.
Come on, let's sing our song.
Mrs. Cat cat, hello Mrs. Cat.
Let's sing our song to Mr. Duck.
Oh Mr. Duck duck, hello Mr. Duck.
Please will you quack for me.
Oh is that Maggie over there?
Little bird bird, hello little bird.
What color is the little bird?
Thank you and bye bye little bird.
I'm here at the park, but where is Maggie?
We have been singing a great song.
Please will you sing for me?
Thank you Maggie and thank you boys and girls.
I’ve got a chocolate in my tommy.
Oh Maggie, it’s nice to sit here.
I am getting a little sleepy.
Come on then, let’s go to bed.
Are you not sleeping in bed?
Hey, show me a sleepy face.
And say, “I am sleepy, sleepy, sleepy.”
I am having a sleepover at Maggie’s place.
But, haha, she lives here up in this tree.
Your nest is a bit small.
So, aaa, time to go to sleep.
I can’t sleep, I am too cold.
Hey, why are you not sleeping.
Because I am too cold Maggie.
Oh no, time for some Maggie magic.
Oh great, I am not cold anymore.
Uf, I am quite hot in this sleeping bag.
I have to get out of this sleeping bag.
Don’t worry Maggie, I am still here.
I need more than just my head.
I've got my head and hands.
My arms, my body, my legs and feet.
Come back here you naughty naughty feet.
There they are sitting on the bench.
Stop being such lazy legs and come here.
I've got two hands and a head.
But I haven't got any arms.
They're my arms dancing to the music.

My legs are dancing, my feet are dancing,
my hands are dancing and my arms are dancing.
My body, my body, my body.
Maggie help me catch my body.
My body, my body.... see you soon.
